data.name: label3.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of players on your server.

data.name: label4.ToolTip
data.value: The password used by admins to grant themselves admin permissions in-game.

data.name: label5.ToolTip
data.value: Sets a password to connect to your server.

data.name: label6.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the public port for the Palworld server. The port would need to be portforwarded and added to firewall inbound and outbound.

data.name: label7.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the public IP address for the Palworld server.

data.name: label8.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables Remote Console (RCON) for server administration.

data.name: label9.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the port for Remote Console (RCON) communication. The port would need to be portforwarded and added to firewall inbound and outbound.

data.name: label10.ToolTip
data.value: Doesn't seem to matter for dedicated servers just set it to None.

data.name: label11.ToolTip
data.value: The rate at which day time passes. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will double the daytime speed.

data.name: label12.ToolTip
data.value: The rate at which nighttime passes. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 0.5, for example, will be half the normal speed of nighttime.

data.name: label13.ToolTip
data.value: The rate at which players gain experience. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2.5, for example, will be 2.5 times faster than the normal experience gain rate.

data.name: label14.ToolTip
data.value: How likely players are to successfully capture pals. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as successful as the normal rate.

data.name: label15.ToolTip
data.value: How frequently new Pals spawn in the world. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as often as the normal rate.

data.name: label16.ToolTip
data.value: How much damage Pals deal. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as strong as the normal rate.

data.name: label17.ToolTip
data.value: How much damage Pals take. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as resistant as the normal rate.

data.name: label18.ToolTip
data.value: How much damage players deal. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as strong as the normal rate.

data.name: label19.ToolTip
data.value: How much damage players take. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as resistant as the normal rate.

data.name: label20.ToolTip
data.value: The rate that players lose hunger saturation. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast to decrease hunger saturation as the normal rate.

data.name: label21.ToolTip
data.value: The rate that players lose stamina during exertion. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast to decrease stamina as the normal rate.

data.name: label22.ToolTip
data.value: How quickly a player's HP will be automatically restored when they are hurt. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as quick as the normal rate.

data.name: label23.ToolTip
data.value: How quickly a player's HP will be automatically restored while sleeping when they are hurt. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast as the normal rate.

data.name: label24.ToolTip
data.value: The rate that Pals lose hunger saturation. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast to decrease saturation as the normal rate.

data.name: label25.ToolTip
data.value: The rate that Pals lose stamina during exertion. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast to decrease stamina as the normal rate.

data.name: label26.ToolTip
data.value: How quickly a Pal's HP will be automatically restored when they are hurt. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as quick as the normal rate.

data.name: label27.ToolTip
data.value: How quickly a Pal's HP will be automatically restored while sleeping when they are hurt. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast as the normal rate.

data.name: label28.ToolTip
data.value: How much damage an object takes when hit. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as much as the normal rate.

data.name: label29.ToolTip
data.value: This determines how much damage built objects will take over time naturally. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as much as the normal rate.

data.name: label30.ToolTip
data.value: The rate at which dropped items are collected. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast as the normal rate.

data.name: label31.ToolTip
data.value: How much HP collectable/breakable items in the world have. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as much as the normal amount.

data.name: label32.ToolTip
data.value: How quickly items in the world like trees, rock, sticks, etc. respawn. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as fast as the normal rate.

data.name: label33.ToolTip
data.value: Sets how often enemies will drop items. The value set in this option is a multiplier, so setting this to 2, for example, will be twice as often as the normal rate.

data.name: label34.ToolTip
data.value:
Sets how much a player loses when they die, valid options include:
None - No items are lost on death Item - All inventory items are dropped, but not equipment ItemAndEquipment - All inventory items and equipment is dropped All (Default) - When players die, they drop their items, equipment, and Pals.

data.name: label38.ToolTip
data.value: Activates or deactivates UNKO (Unidentified Nocturnal Knock-off).

data.name: label39.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables aim assist for controllers.

data.name: label40.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables aim assist for keyboards.

data.name: label41.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of item that can exist on the ground at once on your server. Default is 3000.

data.name: label42.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum number of dropped UNKO items in the game.

data.name: label43.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of base camps that can exist on your server. Default is 128.

data.name: label44.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of workers that can work in a single base camp. Default is 15.

data.name: label45.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum time items remain alive after being dropped.

data.name: label46.ToolTip
data.value: Whether guilds should be automatically disbanded if they inactive for a configured amount of time.

data.name: label47.ToolTip
data.value: If the option above is enabled, guilds will be automatically disbanded after this amount of configured time in hours. Default is 72.

data.name: label48.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of players allowed within a single guild.

data.name: label49.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the default hatching time for Pal eggs.

data.name: label50.ToolTip
data.value: Adjusts the overall work speed in the game.

data.name: label52.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables player versus player (PvP) mode.

data.name: label53.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables the pickup of death penalty drops from other guilds.

data.name: label56.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables the selection of starting locations on the map.

data.name: label57.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables the existence of players after logout.

data.name: label58.ToolTip
data.value: Enables or disables the defense of other guild players.

data.name: label59.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of players allowed within a single party.

data.name: label60.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the region for the Palworld server.

data.name: label62.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the URL for the server's ban list.
